      <head>Carl Sternheim</head>

      <div>
        <p>German playwright and novelist, best known for his comedies, of which 
            <title level="m">Die Hose</title> (The Underpants, 1911) was the most widely acclaimed.</p> 
        
          <p>He was the maternal
          uncle of <ref cRef="entity-000143">Felix-Eberhard von Cube</ref>, whose one-time
          music teacher, <ref cRef="entity-000922">Otto Vrieslander</ref>, was for a time his
          private librarian.</p>
      </div>
